regen.absent_element: alert for interaction level prohibition during startup
regen.new_specification: The TCS shall alert the operator when executing functions beyond the permitted interaction level during Startup State

regen.absent_element: alert details when executing beyond permitted interaction level
regen.new_specification: The system shall provide detailed alerts to the operator when attempting to execute functions beyond the permitted interaction level, including information on the attempted action and the maximum allowed interaction level.

regen.absent_element: alert for interaction levels that are not achievable
regen.new_specification: The TCS shall alert the operator when attempting to execute a function at an interaction level higher than what is supported by the current configuration.

label: The TCS shall inform the operator if the operator attempts to execute a function prohibited as a result of the determined level of interaction.
absence: Warning for execution of functions prohibited according to determined interaction levels
